Due to overcrowding in certain areas of DKR-Texas Memorial Stadium caused by students not sitting in their assigned seats, Texas Athletics is implementing a new football gameday entry protocol for students with tickets in Sections 26, 27 and 28.

Beginning with the San Jose State game on Saturday, Sept. 9, students with tickets in Sections 26-28 must follow these entry procedures:

• Take your game ticket and valid UT ID to Gate 4 of Mike A. Myers Stadium (707 Clyde Littlefield Dr., immediately east of the football stadium) anytime from 9:30 a.m. until halftime.

• Your game ticket, seat location and UT ID will be verified and you will be given a wristband. You must have this wristband to enter Sections 26-28.

• To enter Darrell K Royal-Texas Memorial Stadium, you must present your game ticket and wristband at Gate 25.

• If you enter the stadium prior to obtaining a wristband, you will be asked to go to Gate 4 at Myers Stadium and obtain a wristband, then return to the football stadium through Gate 25.

• To access your seat in Sections 26, 27 or 28, you must show a game ticket and wristband.

• Your wristband must be worn and visible at all times.
